SIMPLE: marbled
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marbled
<hw>Mar"bled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made of,
or faced with, marble.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<er>marbled</er> mansion.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made to resemble marble; veined or spotted like
marble.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Marbled</xex> paper.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Varied with irregular markings,
or witch a confused blending of irregular spots and streaks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Having small flecks of fat interspersed with the
muscle; -- of cuts of meat, especially beef; <as>as, a
well-<ex>marbled</ex> steak</as>. Such marbling improves the flavor of
beef for most people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>marble cake</ent>⟦br⟧
